The issue #26290 fixed with the commit https://github.com/Microsoft/vscode/commit/f7306841f6b3abf59bcbe739672f54f05008c7b9 but I think there is a little flaw shown in the picture above that the `@deprecated` tag and the function description laid in one single line without a space separation and I tried to add a newline between `@deprecated` and description in the .d.ts file like below but it stays the same.
```typescript
declare interface SomeApi {
    /**
     * some function
     * @param para this is a param
     */
    func(para: string);

    /**
     * @deprecated it's old
     * 
     * some old function
     * @param para this is a param for old funtion
     */
    oldFun(para: string);
}
```
@mjbvz 

Sorry for my poor English 😅

This is related to the feature request to assign a problem matcher to a task contributed by a task provider. 

See the quick pick below. Both `gulp: tslint` and `tslint` show up.
![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/172399/25992497/f7f70602-3706-11e7-92e9-ded94978ddbc.png)

tslint is a user defined task,

```
{
	"version": "2.0.0",
	"command": "./node_modules/.bin/gulp",
	"windows": {
		"command": ".\\node_modules\\.bin\\gulp"
	},
	"isShellCommand": true,
	"tasks": [
		{
			"taskName": "ts-watch",
			"args": [],
			"isBuildCommand": true,
			"isWatching": true,
			"problemMatcher": {
				"owner": "typescript",
				"fileLocation": ["absolute"],
				"pattern": {
					"regexp": "^\\*\\*\\* Error: ([^(]+)\\((\\d+|\\d+,\\d+|\\d+,\\d+,\\d+,\\d+)\\): (.*)$",
					"file": 1,
					"location": 2,
					"message": 3
				},
				"watchedTaskBeginsRegExp": "^\\*\\*\\* Starting\\.\\.\\.$",
				"watchedTaskEndsRegExp": "^\\*\\*\\* Finished with \\d+ errors\\.$"
			}
		},
		{
			"taskName": "tslint",
                        "problemMatcher": "$tslint5"
                }
	]
}
```
